description:
&lt;p&gt;Burrnham Community Hospital - Assistant House keeper&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A position has become available from the within our housekeeping team working the following hours:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working various days including weekends and bank holidays&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a 16 bedded ward with rehabilitation beds, a busy Minor injury department, Outpatient department, and various other patient facing departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will require you to work as part of a team and be responsible for the day to day cleaning duties around the hospital and will involve working to a very high standard. You must be a team player with a flexible approach to your work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training in the job role will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return you will receive above basic rates of pay, enhanced payments for weekend work, a generous holiday entitlement and pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits and discussions are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not reapply, unless with prior agreement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this advert may close early if we have enough applicants apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Allison Stone&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hotel Services Team leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Allison.stone@somersetFT.nhs.uk / 01278 773105&lt;/p&gt;
